article.headline: Wofford 97, Chattanooga 58
article.story: CHATTANOOGA, Tenn. -- Noah Dahlman scored 23 points and Cameron Rundles added 21 as Wofford blew out Chattanooga 97-58 on Wednesday night. Brad Loesing scored 13 and Jamar Diggs added 11 for the Terriers (17-12, 13-4 Southern Conference), who defeated Chattanooga 88-56 on Jan. 20. Wofford led by as many as 26, 45-19, in the opening half and shot 70.4 percent from the floor (19 of 27) in the second to extend its lead. Dahlman went 9 of 11 from the field (81.8 percent) and the Terriers finished 35 of 60 (58.3 percent), including 12 of 23 from 3-point range (52.2 percent). Chris Early scored 13, Dontay Hampton added 12 and Keegan Bell 10 for the Mocs (15-15, 11-6), who shot 25 percent from 3-point range (8 of 32) and were outrebounded 42-28. The 97-point outburst by the Terriers is their highest point total since a 99-44 win over Toccoa Falls on Dec. 8, 2004.
